== English ==
===Etymology===
From Old French [[camphore]] or medieval Latin [[camphora]], from Arabic {{ARchar|[[كافور]]}} (kāfūr), from Malay [[kapur]], ultimately from Sanskrit [[कर्पुर]] (karpura).

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈkæmfə/}}

=== Noun ===
'''camphor''' {{uncountable}}

# a white transparent waxy crystalline [[isoprenoid]] [[ketone]], with a strong pungent odour, used in pharmacy

